<p><span style=3D"font-size: 20.0px;letter-spacing: -0.008em;">Overview</sp=
an></p>
<p>This page describes the common data types defined by <span>Westpac Mesh&=
nbsp;</span>and their typical usage.&nbsp; All APIs are expected to use the=
se common data types where applicable.&nbsp; New data types will be added t=
o this page over time as they are discovered.</p>
<h2 id=3D"CommonDataTypes-PrimitiveDataTypes">Primitive Data Types</h2>
<p>Westpac Mesh API primitive data types are based on the Swagger Specifica=
tion v2 that can be found&nbsp;<a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://g=
ithub.com/OAI/OpenAPI-Specification/blob/master/versions/2.0.md#data-types"=
 rel=3D"nofollow">here</a>, but with some exceptions as indicated in the ta=
ble below.</p>
<p>Primitives have an optional modifier property&nbsp;<code>format</code>. =
Swagger uses several known formats to refine the data type being used.</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"relative-table wrapped confluenceTable" style=3D"width: 99.=
94%;">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 5.87%;">
<col style=3D"width: 3.91%;">
<col style=3D"width: 4.33%;">
<col style=3D"width: 85.86%;">
</colgroup>
<thead>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><p>Common Name</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><code>type</code></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><code>format</code></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><p>Comments</p></th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">float</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>string</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>regex</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>There is a known issue in JSON serialisation/=
deserialisation with respect to float and double numbers which causes a los=
s of precision.</p><p>Therefore, all fractional numbers will be declared as=
 strings with a format describing the actual number format.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">double</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>string</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>regex</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">As per above.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">date</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">string</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">date</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><span>As defined by&nbsp;</span><c=
ode>full-date</code><span>&nbsp;-&nbsp;</span><a href=3D"https://www.rfc-ed=
itor.org/rfc/rfc3339" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">RFC3339</a><=
span>&nbsp;- format&nbsp;YYYY-MM-DD</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">dateTime</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">string</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">date-time</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><span>As defined by&nbsp;</span=
><code>date-time</code><span>&nbsp;-&nbsp;</span><a href=3D"https://www.rfc=
-editor.org/rfc/rfc3339" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">RFC3339</=
a><span>&nbsp;- format&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"=
>YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss.fffZ</span></p><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">N=
ote:&nbsp;<span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Use ISO8601 for date time f=
ormatting, i.e.&nbsp;2012-01-01T12:00:00Z.&nbsp; Note that the date time va=
lue must be returned as UTC time not local time</span></span></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">time</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">string</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">time</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">As defined by&nbsp;<code>full-time=
</code>&nbsp;-&nbsp;<a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"http://xml2rfc.ietf.=
org/public/rfc/html/rfc3339.html#anchor14" rel=3D"nofollow">I</a>SO8601&nbs=
p;-&nbsp;format&nbsp;<span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><span style=3D"colo=
r: rgb(0,0,0);"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"b18a2549-=
61ea-43be-a32f-41daecba7dc4">hh:mm:ss.fffZ</span></span></span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">integer</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">integer</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">int32</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">long</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">integer</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">int64</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">string</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">string</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">boolean</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">boolean</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">enum</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">string</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><span class=3D"inline-comment-m=
arker" data-ref=3D"448a16a4-2654-4a15-bf49-97b6a19f52ea">A fixed list of po=
ssible values. If this field is used in conjunction with the defaultValue f=
ield, then the default value MUST be one of the values defined in the enum.=
 All values in an enum must adhere to the specified&nbsp;</span><strong><co=
de><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"448a16a4-2654-4a15-bf4=
9-97b6a19f52ea">type</span></code><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" dat=
a-ref=3D"448a16a4-2654-4a15-bf49-97b6a19f52ea">.&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span c=
lass=3D"st"><em><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"448a16a4-=
2654-4a15-bf49-97b6a19f52ea">enums</span></em><span class=3D"inline-comment=
-marker" data-ref=3D"448a16a4-2654-4a15-bf49-97b6a19f52ea"> are not properl=
y defined when </span><em><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D=
"448a16a4-2654-4a15-bf49-97b6a19f52ea">spaces</span></em><span class=3D"inl=
ine-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"448a16a4-2654-4a15-bf49-97b6a19f52ea"> appe=
ar in the string . </span></span></strong><span class=3D"st"><span class=3D=
"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"448a16a4-2654-4a15-bf49-97b6a19f52ea">S=
o </span></span><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"448a16a4-=
2654-4a15-bf49-97b6a19f52ea">replace space with underscore or words without=
 a seperator. eg:'Not Selected' must be defined as 'NOT_SELECTED' or not_se=
lected or Not_Selected&nbsp; or NotSelected</span><strong><br></strong></p>=
<p><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"448a16a4-2654-4a15-bf4=
9-97b6a19f52ea">Name enum values in business terms not code. Do not define =
enums as 0,1 etc . It should be named in proper business terms.</span></p><=
p><u><strong><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"448a16a4-265=
4-4a15-bf49-97b6a19f52ea">Keys things:</span></strong></u></p>
<ul>
<li><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"448a16a4-2654-4a15-bf=
49-97b6a19f52ea">Dots are not allowed in Enum values.</span></li>
<li><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"448a16a4-2654-4a15-bf=
49-97b6a19f52ea">Use Upper cases for abbreviations/acronyms</span></li>
<li><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"448a16a4-2654-4a15-bf=
49-97b6a19f52ea">Use _ instead of spaces/dots or combine the words</span></=
li>
<li><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"448a16a4-2654-4a15-bf=
49-97b6a19f52ea">Define enum values in business terms.</span></li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<h2 id=3D"CommonDataTypes-CommonDataTypes"><span style=3D"font-size: 20.0px=
;">Common Data Types<br></span></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped relative-table confluenceTable" style=3D"width: 99.=
861%;">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 9.24791%;">
<col style=3D"width: 13.0919%;">
<col style=3D"width: 14.039%;">
<col style=3D"width: 15.4875%;">
<col style=3D"width: 14.9304%;">
<col style=3D"width: 33.0362%;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Data Type</strong></p></th>
<th colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTh">Description</th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Composition</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Comment</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Example</strong></p></th>
<th colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTh">yaml</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h4 id=3D"CommonDataTypes-Identifi=
er"><strong>Identifier</strong></h4></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><span>General Identification struc=
ture to capture the identification scheme and the identification value to u=
niquely reference a resource</span></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>"id": The string containing the=
 identifier value</p><p>"idScheme": The identification scheme used</p></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Refer to separate section on commo=
n identifier structures</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: js; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">{=20
  id: "12345678901",=20
  idScheme: "CustomerInternalId"=20
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
</div></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p>Below syntax can be used if identifier is used in body :</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: yaml; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Custome=
rId:
  type: object
  required:
    - id
    - idScheme
  properties:
    id:
=09  type: string
=09idScheme:
      description: &gt;
        Scheme of the Id eg: CustomerInternalId/CustomerNumber/PartyUID/Ext=
ernalSystemCustId.
        - CustomerInternalId is Customer Id from the Source System eg. GCIS=
Key or CISKey
        - PartyUID - Party Universal ID , generated in GCM.=20
        - CustomerNumber is Internet Bank Client id.=20
        - ExternalSystemCustId is Customer Id from External Source System.
      type: string
      enum:
        - CustomerInternalId
        - CustomerNumber
        - PartyUID
        - ExternalSystemCustomerId</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><h4 id=3D"CommonDataTypes-CurrencyAmount"><stron=
g>CurrencyAmount</strong></h4></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">A numerical amount used to represe=
nt money</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>=E2=80=9CcurrencyCode=E2=80=9D: String contai=
ning the three character [ISO 4217] code</p><p>=E2=80=9Camount=E2=80=9D: <s=
trong>String</strong> value of the total number of units, default is to 2 d=
ecimal places, except for currencies that require more as per ISO 4217, i.e=
. Chile.</p><p>Negative amounts must be prefixed with minus sign. ('-')</p>=
</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Currency code is implied to be =E2=80=98AUD=
=E2=80=99. Might not be required internally, but will be required for Open =
APIs in future.</p><p>As at March 2018, the maximum number of decimal place=
s in use for any international currency is 4</p><p>Note, =E2=80=98$=E2=80=
=99 or any other currency indicator MUST not be returned in amount</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>{=E2=80=9CcurrencyCode=E2=80=9D: =E2=80=9DAUD=
=E2=80=9D,</p><p>=E2=80=9Camount=E2=80=9D: "123.45"}</p></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence"> currenc=
yAmount:
    description:  A qualified amount and denomination of a monetary value.
    type: object
    properties:
     amount:
        type: string
        pattern: '^[-]?\d{1,13}\.\d{1,4}$'
      currencyCode:
        description:  The ISO4217 currency code of the currency
        type: string</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h4 id=3D"CommonDataTypes-Balance"=
><strong>Balance</strong></h4></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><span>Based on CurrencyAmount with=
 addition of 'position' to indicate if the balance is in Credit (CR) or Deb=
it (DR)</span></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>=E2=80=9CcurrencyCode=E2=80=9D:=
 String containing the three character [ISO 4217] code</p><p>=E2=80=9Camoun=
t=E2=80=9D: <strong>String</strong> value of the total number of units, def=
ault is to 2 decimal places, except for currencies that require more as per=
 ISO 4217, i.e. Chile.</p><p>"position": Indicates if the amount in CR/DR</=
p><p><br></p></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Currency code is implied to be =
=E2=80=98AUD=E2=80=99. Might not be required internally, but will be requir=
ed for Open APIs in future.</p><p><span>As at March 2018, the maximum numbe=
r of decimal places in use for any international currency is 4</span></p><p=
>Note, =E2=80=98$=E2=80=99 or any other currency indicator MUST not be retu=
rned in amount</p></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>"currentBalance": {</p><p style=
=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;">"currencyCode": "AUD",</p><p style=3D"margin-left=
: 30.0px;">"amount": "123.45",</p><p style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;">"positi=
on": "CR"</p><p>}</p></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence"> current=
Balance:
    description: balance amount details.
    type: object
    properties:
      amount:
        type: string
        pattern: '^\d{1,13}\.\d{1,4}$'
      currencyCode:
        type: string
      position:
        type: string
        enum:
        - CR
        - DR</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><h4 id=3D"CommonDataTypes-TimePeriod"><strong>Ti=
mePeriod</strong></h4></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><span>A duration of time expressed=
 in terms of the number of units of time, such as years, months, days</span=
></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p>Expressed according to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601=
#Durations" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">ISO8601 duration forma=
t</a>, as follows:</p>
<p>P[n]Y[n]M[n]DT[n]H[n]M[n]S or P[n]W</p>
<p>where</p>
<ul>
<li>P, Y, M, W, D, T, H, M, and S are designators for each of the date and =
time elements</li>
<li><p>[n] is replaced by the number of units for each date and time elemen=
t</p></li>
<li><p>P is the duration designator (for period) placed at the start of the=
 duration representation</p></li>
<li><p>Y is the year designator that follows the value for the number of ye=
ars</p></li>
<li><p>M is the month designator that follows the value for the number of m=
onths</p></li>
<li><p>W is the week designator that follows the value for the number of we=
eks</p></li>
<li><p>D is the day designator that follows the value for the number of day=
s</p></li>
<li><p>T is the time designator that precedes the time components of the re=
presentation</p></li>
<li><p>H is the hour designator that follows the value for the number of ho=
urs</p></li>
<li><p>M is the minute designator that follows the value for the number of =
minutes</p></li>
<li>S is the second designator that follows the value for the number of sec=
onds</li>
</ul>
</div></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>"fixedLoanTerm": "P5Y"</p><p>"expectedWaitTim=
e": "PT1M"</p></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>remainingTerm:<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; description: Term for this liability. Term value sent as per=
iod E.g.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; P24M/P2Y&nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; type: string<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; pattern: '^P[\d]Y[\d]M$'</p><p><br></p><p>If returned only i=
n years then use pattern as ,&nbsp;'P[n]Y'</p><p><br></p><p>If returned onl=
y in months , then use&nbsp;</p><p>'P[n]M'</p><p><br></p><p><span style=3D"=
color: rgb(32,33,34);">"PT1M" indicates the duration of one minute&nbsp;</s=
pan></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h4 id=3D"CommonDataTypes-Timeoffs=
etsfromUTC"><strong><span class=3D"mw-headline">Time offsets from UTC</span=
></strong></h4></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">An offset from UTC represented usi=
ng a string.</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Negative&nbsp;UTC offsets&nbsp;=
describe a&nbsp;time zone&nbsp;west of&nbsp;UTC=C2=B100:00, where the&nbsp;=
civil time&nbsp;is behind (or earlier) than&nbsp;UTC&nbsp;so the zone desig=
nator will look like "=E2=88=9203:00"</p><p>Positive&nbsp;UTC offsets&nbsp;=
describe a&nbsp;time zone&nbsp;east of&nbsp;UTC=C2=B100:00, where the&nbsp;=
civil time&nbsp;is ahead (or later) than&nbsp;UTC&nbsp;so the zone designat=
or will look like "+02:00"</p></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br><p>"timeOffsetFromUTC<span sty=
le=3D"letter-spacing: 0.0px;">" =3D "-02:30"</span></p></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>timeOffsetFromUTC<span style=3D=
"letter-spacing: 0.0px;">:</span></p>&nbsp; type: string<br>
 &nbsp; description: An ISO8601-valid string representing the offset from U=
TC<br>
 &nbsp; example: "+05:30"<br>
 &nbsp; pattern: "=C2=B1[hh]:[mm]"</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><h4 id=3D"CommonDataTypes-Percentage"><strong>Pe=
rcentage</strong></h4></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><span>A decimal with a range from =
0 to 100.00 that represents a ratio</span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><br></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><br></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>=E2=80=9CpercentageComplete=E2=80=9D: "25.75"=
</p></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h4 id=3D"CommonDataTypes-Address"=
><strong>Address</strong></h4></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><span>General&nbsp; structure to c=
apture the postal and physical address.</span></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>"address":{</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&=
nbsp; "addressLine1": "string",</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "addressLine2": "s=
tring",</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "addressLine3": "string",</p><p>&nbsp;&nbs=
p;&nbsp; "addressType": "string",</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "buildingName": =
"string",</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "unitNumber": "string",</p><p>&nbsp;&nbs=
p;&nbsp; "streetName": "string",</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "streetNumber": "=
string",</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "streetType": "string",</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp=
;&nbsp; "suburb": "string",</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "city": "string",</p><=
p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "country": "string",</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "postalC=
ode": "string",</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "state": "string",</p><p>&nbsp;&nb=
sp;&nbsp; "status": "string"</p><p>}</p></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h4 id=3D"CommonDataTypes-LogicalO=
perator">Logical Operator</h4></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>when applying a filter to a res=
ource the default logical operator is AND. You can use this data type to ch=
ange the behaviour to OR.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><br></p><p>In the given example=
, the resource will return all customers who are having age =3D 75&nbsp; OR=
 name =3D abc OR country&nbsp;=3D AUS</p></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>GET /customers? $logicalOperato=
r=3DOR &amp; age =3D 75 &amp; name =3D abc &amp; country =3D AUS</p></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>$logicalOperator:</p><p>&nbsp; =
type: string</p><p>&nbsp; enum:</p><p>&nbsp;- OR</p><p>&nbsp;- AND</p><p>&n=
bsp;&nbsp;</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
